00:17.818 --> 00:20.064
- You gotta be kidding me.

00:20.088 --> 00:22.199
Jessica, why?

00:22.223 --> 00:26.103
- Well, I don't
need you anymore.

00:37.538 --> 00:40.508
♪♪♪

00:53.254 --> 00:56.224
♪♪♪

01:03.864 --> 01:06.534
♪♪♪

01:12.273 --> 01:15.719
♪♪♪

01:15.743 --> 01:17.821
- So I told the woman,

01:17.845 --> 01:19.856
"With what my husband and I
have donated to the museum over

01:19.880 --> 01:22.526
the years, we should be part
of the permanent collection."

01:22.550 --> 01:25.519
♪♪♪

01:36.164 --> 01:38.642
Oh, look who's here.

01:38.666 --> 01:41.578
- Jessica, I'm so
sorry I'm late.

01:41.602 --> 01:44.148
Have you talked to Michael?

01:44.172 --> 01:46.883
- He's still in Dubai trying
to land the wealthy Arabs.

01:46.907 --> 01:49.453
Hopefully, he'll be back
soon with some good news.

01:49.477 --> 01:52.389
- Come, let's talk in private.

01:57.285 --> 02:00.530
- Simone, level with me. How bad is it?
Robert won't tell me.

02:00.554 --> 02:02.866
- The DA wants to see Michael
as soon as he's back.

02:02.890 --> 02:06.336
Investors are breathing
down his neck.

02:06.360 --> 02:08.472
Must be the same with Robert.

02:08.496 --> 02:10.440
- You know how he is.
Always sure he can pull

02:10.464 --> 02:13.410
a rabbit out of his hat.
- Well, if anyone can,

02:13.434 --> 02:15.912
it's Robert.
- What is it I can do?

02:15.936 --> 02:19.383
- What happens if Michael
can't raise enough cash?

02:19.407 --> 02:22.352
- Well, I'm sure he will.
- Robert, what is happening with

02:22.376 --> 02:23.820
your investors? They're been
waiting on returns. How much

02:23.844 --> 02:26.356
do you need to come up with?
- I'm going to get

02:26.380 --> 02:27.957
a glass of wine.

02:27.981 --> 02:31.695
Why are you so upset?

02:31.719 --> 02:34.564
- Because I want
to know the truth!

02:34.588 --> 02:37.334
How much trouble are we in?

02:37.358 --> 02:39.803
- Baby, trust me,

02:39.827 --> 02:41.838
you have nothing to worry about.

02:41.862 --> 02:45.342
Michael and I have
everything under control.

02:45.366 --> 02:47.568
- Don't sell me, Robert.

02:49.703 --> 02:51.848
- We can talk about this
later, but in the meantime,

02:51.872 --> 02:53.983
we have guests...

03:05.819 --> 03:06.996
- Been doing that for years.

03:07.020 --> 03:08.898
- Hey, you can't come in here.

03:08.922 --> 03:10.834
- Robert Calders?

03:10.858 --> 03:12.593
FBI.

03:16.497 --> 03:19.443
- What the hell is this?
- Nice place you have here.

03:19.467 --> 03:21.511
- You can't just barge
in here like this.

03:21.535 --> 03:24.648
- Robert Calders, you are under
arrest for investment fraud.

03:24.672 --> 03:27.317
- I told you.

03:27.341 --> 03:29.253
I told you this would happen!
I told you

03:29.277 --> 03:31.455
this would happen! How
could you do this to me?!

03:31.479 --> 03:34.924
Robert, you promised
me we'd be OK!

03:34.948 --> 03:36.784
I told you! I told you!

03:38.586 --> 03:40.854
♪♪♪

03:58.439 --> 04:00.841
♪♪♪

04:06.847 --> 04:09.326
- It's more off the back.
- OK, I got it.

04:09.350 --> 04:12.662
♪♪♪

04:12.686 --> 04:14.522
That's it.

04:18.791 --> 04:21.605
- My parents are in
Geneva until the end

04:21.629 --> 04:23.940
of the month, so we have the
whole place to ourselves.

04:23.964 --> 04:26.009
- At least, you have
your folks to fall

04:26.033 --> 04:28.345
back on.

04:28.369 --> 04:30.714
I don't know what I'm gonna do.
- Michael's lawyer says

04:30.738 --> 04:32.749
they could be out in
three to five years.

04:32.773 --> 04:36.019
It's really not that long.
- Simone, they took everything!

04:36.043 --> 04:38.655
- Robert must have left
something in your name.

04:38.679 --> 04:41.458
- One account.

04:41.482 --> 04:44.494
86,000 and change. - Jessica,

04:44.518 --> 04:46.563
you're the strongest
woman I know.

04:46.587 --> 04:48.465
You'll bounce back from
this; we both will.

04:48.489 --> 04:50.700
And if you need money...

04:50.724 --> 04:52.993
- Simone, please, you've
already been way too generous.

04:55.429 --> 04:58.408
- Well, at least, we don't
have kids to worry about.

05:00.634 --> 05:03.036
- Yeah.

05:30.498 --> 05:31.932
♪♪♪

05:34.868 --> 05:37.405
"Allison."

05:48.916 --> 05:50.960
- It was a nice funeral.

05:50.984 --> 05:52.853
- Your dad wasn't one
for being showy.

05:55.055 --> 05:57.667
- Mr. Martin,

05:57.691 --> 05:59.803
your eulogy

05:59.827 --> 06:01.871
was beautiful.

06:01.895 --> 06:04.974
- Cam was like a brother to me.

06:06.700 --> 06:09.413
Come here.

06:09.437 --> 06:12.749
- He really loved you.

06:12.773 --> 06:14.742
- I can't imagine how hard
this must be for you.

06:17.044 --> 06:19.756
It feels like just yesterday
we were here for your mother.

06:19.780 --> 06:21.858
- It's been three years.

06:21.882 --> 06:24.585
♪♪♪

06:36.864 --> 06:39.876
Do you think Mom and Dad
are together again?

06:39.900 --> 06:42.912
- I do. You?

06:42.936 --> 06:44.881
- I don't know.

06:44.905 --> 06:46.874
I hope so.

06:52.846 --> 06:54.858
- I really wish you girls

06:54.882 --> 06:56.626
will reconsider coming
to stay with us.

06:56.650 --> 06:58.495
You would love New York.

06:58.519 --> 07:01.130
And your uncle, the boys;
we'd be thrilled to have you.

07:01.154 --> 07:03.132
- Aunt Monica, you
don't have to.

07:03.156 --> 07:05.835
We'll be fine. We're
not kids anymore.

07:05.859 --> 07:09.038
- No, you're not.

07:09.062 --> 07:10.974
You've had to grow
up way too fast.

07:10.998 --> 07:12.733
- Girls, I'll see you
back at the house.

07:18.271 --> 07:19.916
Jessica?

07:19.940 --> 07:22.118
- Long time no see.

07:22.142 --> 07:24.220
- What the hell are
you doing here?

07:24.244 --> 07:26.055
- I read about Cameron's
plane crash in the paper,

07:26.079 --> 07:28.492
and I just had to come.
Hadn't heard

07:28.516 --> 07:31.928
about his wife though.
Cancer? So sad.

07:31.952 --> 07:34.598
- What do you want?

07:34.622 --> 07:37.000
- I want to see Allison.

07:37.024 --> 07:38.992
I want to see my daughter.

07:41.695 --> 07:43.740
- Allison,

07:43.764 --> 07:45.509
you have to eat.

07:45.533 --> 07:47.777
- I'm not hungry.

07:47.801 --> 07:51.114
- I'll see you guys later.
- Wait, what about breakfast?

07:51.138 --> 07:53.550
- I'm meeting friends;
I'll grab something later.

07:53.574 --> 07:55.218
- You should spend
time with your sister.

07:55.242 --> 07:57.186
- I do spend time with her.

07:57.210 --> 07:59.823
- I'm alright. It's OK.

07:59.847 --> 08:01.958
- You should get out
of the house too.

08:01.982 --> 08:04.117
Why don't you text Erica?
- I will.

08:06.987 --> 08:08.998
- Bye.

08:09.022 --> 08:11.000
- You signed away your rights

08:11.024 --> 08:12.869
as a mother the day
you gave Allie up

08:12.893 --> 08:14.804
for adoption.

08:14.828 --> 08:16.906
- Yes, I'm aware.

08:16.930 --> 08:19.142
It was the most difficult
decision I've ever made.

08:19.166 --> 08:21.911
And the worst.
- Sleeping with your married

08:21.935 --> 08:23.647
boss must rank pretty
high up there.

08:23.671 --> 08:26.950
Hey, sorry to interrupt.

08:26.974 --> 08:29.152
I heard from the guys. Can I
see you after this meeting?

08:29.176 --> 08:31.955
- I'll come down to your office
as soon as we're finished here.

08:31.979 --> 08:33.756
- Thanks.

08:33.780 --> 08:35.792
- Listen,

08:35.816 --> 08:38.794
I didn't come here
to dig up the past.

08:38.818 --> 08:41.264
I made a choice, and I've lived
with it for a long time.

08:41.288 --> 08:43.667
♪♪♪ But things have changed.

08:43.691 --> 08:46.135
I'm a different woman now.

08:46.159 --> 08:49.005
- People don't change.

08:49.029 --> 08:51.040
- I don't expect you

08:51.064 --> 08:52.876
to understand or even trust me,

08:52.900 --> 08:55.111
but Allison is a child

08:55.135 --> 08:58.114
and she just lost the only
parents she's ever known.

08:58.138 --> 09:00.717
Don't you think she deserves
the right to get to know

09:00.741 --> 09:02.251
the only one she's got left?
- Not if that parent

09:02.275 --> 09:04.011
is only interested
in her inheritance.

09:06.246 --> 09:08.191
- I could have approached
her directly, you know?

09:08.215 --> 09:12.028
But I came to you
first out of respect.

09:12.052 --> 09:15.331
Cameron trusted you to do
what's best for Allison,

09:15.355 --> 09:17.801
and that's all I want

09:17.825 --> 09:20.036
is to do what's best
for our daughter.

09:20.060 --> 09:23.740
- If Allison wants,
you can see her.

09:23.764 --> 09:25.975
But I'll be watching you.

09:25.999 --> 09:28.111
- Be my guest.

09:28.135 --> 09:30.179
I have nothing to hide.

09:30.203 --> 09:32.072
- Everything has
something to hide.

09:35.342 --> 09:37.687
I got you.

09:37.711 --> 09:39.656
OK. Here you go.

09:41.982 --> 09:43.651
- Hi, Sydni!

09:46.787 --> 09:49.056
- Daddy, higher!
- Here we go, sweetie. Come on!

09:52.125 --> 09:54.838
It's gonna be fun! Ha! Ha! Ha!

10:00.400 --> 10:02.335
- Not much of a big
sister, are you?

10:05.939 --> 10:07.884
Leave a message.

10:07.908 --> 10:10.754
- Cole, we need to talk.

10:10.778 --> 10:12.822
Tomorrow.

10:12.846 --> 10:15.749
♪♪♪

10:26.994 --> 10:29.038
- I didn't know

10:29.062 --> 10:31.975
Dad fished.
- Yeah. Back in the day.

10:31.999 --> 10:33.977
We used to go upstate
every spring.

10:34.001 --> 10:36.112
- Why did you stop?
- I guess

10:36.136 --> 10:38.882
we just couldn't find the time.
- Sorry I'm late.

10:38.906 --> 10:41.217
Traffic.

10:41.241 --> 10:43.376
- Let's get started.

10:46.279 --> 10:48.324
There's a lot of details
that we can go over later,

10:48.348 --> 10:50.293
but the long and short of
it is that you're each

10:50.317 --> 10:52.361
entitled to half of
your father's estate

10:52.385 --> 10:55.732
which, all told, is valued
at right around $80 million.

10:55.756 --> 10:57.190
Allison...

10:59.192 --> 11:01.404
your funds are to be
held in trust until

11:01.428 --> 11:03.406
you turn 18 and then,
as you can see,

11:03.430 --> 11:05.775
there's a tiered
structure of access:

11:05.799 --> 11:07.744
a certain amount once
you graduate college,

11:07.768 --> 11:09.713
more once you've started
a career and the rest

11:09.737 --> 11:12.181
in yearly instalments
until your 40th birthday.

11:12.205 --> 11:15.151
Until then, there's a healthy stipend
to cover all living expenses.

11:15.175 --> 11:17.821
Anything extra that comes up,
you have to get cleared by me.

11:17.845 --> 11:19.022
- OK.

11:19.046 --> 11:21.925
- Sydni...

11:21.949 --> 11:25.161
you're under the same tiered
structure as your sister.

11:25.185 --> 11:27.196
- Wait, I have to go to college

11:27.220 --> 11:29.365
and get a job before I
can get my inheritance?

11:29.389 --> 11:32.101
- Part of it anyway. Your
father wanted to make sure

11:32.125 --> 11:35.038
that your future was as
secure as it could be.

11:35.062 --> 11:38.041
- Great. Thanks, Dad.

11:38.065 --> 11:40.209
- There's something else
that you both need to know.

11:40.233 --> 11:43.379
Something your father wanted you to know.
- What is it?

11:43.403 --> 11:46.439
♪♪♪- He wrote you each a letter.

11:59.853 --> 12:01.998
- Well, this certainly is

12:02.022 --> 12:03.933
a lot nicer than the joints
we used to frequent.

12:03.957 --> 12:05.969
- Yes, well, I have acquired

12:05.993 --> 12:08.371
a taste for the finer things.
- As have I.

12:08.395 --> 12:11.274
So how about we head up to
your room and compare notes?

12:11.298 --> 12:13.877
- Tempting.

12:13.901 --> 12:15.502
But that's not why I
wanted you to come.

12:19.139 --> 12:21.241
- Bourbon. Single
barrel, please.

12:25.813 --> 12:27.347
Thank you.

12:30.517 --> 12:32.385
- Lawyer's gonna be a problem.

12:34.221 --> 12:37.233
- Want me to solve
it like last time?

12:37.257 --> 12:39.468
- No. I think this calls

12:39.492 --> 12:42.295
for something a little
more sophisticated.

12:44.497 --> 12:46.843
My dearest Allison,

12:46.867 --> 12:48.912
I very much hoped to
have this conversation

12:48.936 --> 12:51.280
with you in person when you
were old enough to understand.

12:51.304 --> 12:54.150
Your mom's passing had
me thinking a great deal

12:54.174 --> 12:57.987
about my own mortality, and
about you and your sister.

12:58.011 --> 13:00.189
Sydni, you know your
little sister's adopted,

13:00.213 --> 13:02.959
and you know I love her
just as much as I love you,

13:02.983 --> 13:05.028
but there's something
you don't know,

13:05.052 --> 13:07.263
something your mother and I
have decided to keep from you

13:07.287 --> 13:10.399
and from Allison.
I had an affair.

13:10.423 --> 13:13.169
It didn't last long.
I came to my senses

13:13.193 --> 13:16.105
and broke it off. But
the woman I was with,

13:16.129 --> 13:19.375
she got pregnant. She got
pregnant with you, Allison.

13:19.399 --> 13:21.878
I thought for sure your mother
would leave me, but she didn't.

13:21.902 --> 13:24.881
She forgave me. So much so

13:24.905 --> 13:27.183
that when Allison's birth mother
told me she couldn't keep her,

13:27.207 --> 13:29.042
your mother and I
decided to adopt her.

13:31.211 --> 13:33.356
Not telling you the
truth, not telling you

13:33.380 --> 13:36.525
that I'm your father by
blood, not just by adoption,

13:36.549 --> 13:39.328
has been almost unbearable.

13:39.352 --> 13:41.630
I pray that you'll forgive
me and that you'll

13:41.654 --> 13:44.000
continue to love and take
care of your sister.

13:44.024 --> 13:46.269
I love you, Allie.

13:46.293 --> 13:49.472
With all my heart. I always
have and always will

13:49.496 --> 13:51.407
in this life and the next.

13:51.431 --> 13:53.333
Love, Dad.

14:04.677 --> 14:08.157
- Did you know?
- I had no idea. Aaron?

14:08.181 --> 14:10.326
- As your father's attorney,
I had to respect his wishes.

14:10.350 --> 14:12.145
- You lied to me?!
- I'm sorry, but

14:12.157 --> 14:13.963
it's what your parents wanted.

14:13.987 --> 14:16.265
He was going to tell you.
- When?

14:16.289 --> 14:18.501
- I don't know. But I
know it tore him up

14:18.525 --> 14:20.493
inside.

14:22.595 --> 14:25.441
- This is so messed up.

14:25.465 --> 14:28.477
- Look, I realize that this is
a lot to take in right now,

14:28.501 --> 14:30.679
but there is another factor
that we have to discuss.

14:30.703 --> 14:33.149
- What n? You're gonna tell us

14:33.173 --> 14:35.451
our parents were in the CIA?
- The woman who...

14:35.475 --> 14:38.687
Allison's birth mother,
she wants to see you.

14:38.711 --> 14:41.414
♪♪♪

14:43.984 --> 14:46.329
- And with the lawyer out
of the way, how long

14:46.353 --> 14:48.631
before you can adopt the kid?
- I told you,

14:48.655 --> 14:50.566
I still need a little more
time to win her over.

14:50.590 --> 14:53.937
Hopefully not too long.
- You know, uh,

14:53.961 --> 14:56.572
I don't work on contingency
for just anyone.

14:56.596 --> 14:58.707
- A million dollars is a
pretty big contingency.

14:58.731 --> 15:00.944
- Two.

15:00.968 --> 15:03.246
Excuse me?

15:03.270 --> 15:06.682
- Two million.

15:06.706 --> 15:09.385
Come on. I read in the paper
what this guy is worth.

15:09.409 --> 15:13.422
You can afford it.
Look, if it makes you

15:13.446 --> 15:16.092
feel any better, I'll throw
in the rental car for free.

15:26.159 --> 15:29.205
- I can't believe they would
just lie to us like that.

15:29.229 --> 15:31.740
- I know. I mean, I understand
maybe when we're little,

15:31.764 --> 15:34.577
but you'd think after Mom died,
Dad would have manned up

15:34.601 --> 15:37.046
and told us the truth.

15:37.070 --> 15:39.082
- Every time Mom looked at me,

15:39.106 --> 15:41.617
she had to be reminded
of him cheating.

15:41.641 --> 15:43.752
- Allie, Mom loved you.

15:43.776 --> 15:45.989
She couldn't have
loved you more, OK?

15:46.013 --> 15:48.124
- I wish I could talk
to her about all this.

15:48.148 --> 15:51.027
- I know.
- When Mom died,

15:51.051 --> 15:53.229
that was the first time
I ever really thought

15:53.253 --> 15:55.198
about having a birth mom.

15:55.222 --> 15:57.124
- Come here.

16:01.261 --> 16:03.206
So you think you're
gonna meet her?

16:03.230 --> 16:05.241
- I guess so.

16:05.265 --> 16:06.675
I mean, why not, right?

16:06.699 --> 16:08.577
- Why not?

16:08.601 --> 16:11.971
♪♪♪

16:33.126 --> 16:35.228
♪♪♪

16:38.331 --> 16:40.676
- "To my daughter Allison...

16:40.700 --> 16:42.635
♪♪♪

16:45.305 --> 16:47.340
Oh my!

16:52.579 --> 16:54.781
To my daughter Allison.

16:59.152 --> 17:02.122
♪♪♪

17:11.564 --> 17:13.500
Perfect.

17:20.173 --> 17:22.451
I'm glad you agreed to see me.

17:22.474 --> 17:24.211
I know this is a lot to process.

17:26.378 --> 17:28.791
First, I would just like to say
how sorry I am for your loss.

17:28.815 --> 17:31.660
Losses.

17:31.684 --> 17:34.197
Can't imagine how difficult
this is for you.

17:34.221 --> 17:35.798
For both of you.

17:35.822 --> 17:38.391
- Thanks.

17:40.127 --> 17:41.737
- Your father was
a wonderful man.

17:41.761 --> 17:45.474
- I thought so.
- Allison, please don't

17:45.498 --> 17:48.344
judge him too harshly.
He made a mistake.

17:48.368 --> 17:50.813
- How long were
you two together?

17:50.837 --> 17:54.117
- I don't think the details of
the relationship are important.

17:54.141 --> 17:56.385
- It's alright. She
deserves to know.

17:56.409 --> 18:00.256
I was helping your father
out with a project at work.

18:00.280 --> 18:02.725
It was early on, and the
company was struggling.

18:02.749 --> 18:04.584
He was under a lot of pressure.

18:07.454 --> 18:10.899
So, we were working
late one night, and...

18:10.923 --> 18:13.569
and one night turned into a few.

18:13.593 --> 18:16.805
Then it was over.

18:16.829 --> 18:18.907
He told me he had a
wife and a daughter,

18:18.931 --> 18:20.843
and he wanted to be
with them, not me.

18:20.867 --> 18:22.911
- Did you love him?

18:22.935 --> 18:25.881
- I did.

18:25.905 --> 18:28.351
Least I thought I did.

18:28.375 --> 18:31.144
I don't know, I'd never
been in love before, so...

18:32.745 --> 18:36.359
- So... why?

18:36.383 --> 18:39.386
- Why did you give her up?

18:42.189 --> 18:44.867
- Allison, I was so
messed up back then.

18:44.891 --> 18:47.736
Drinking, drugs. - You seemed

18:47.760 --> 18:50.706
to have cleaned up your act
somewhere along the way.

18:50.730 --> 18:53.542
Why didn't you reach out then?

18:53.566 --> 18:57.246
- Because I promised your mother
and father I'd stay away.

18:57.270 --> 18:59.782
Believe me, there are many times
I wanted to break that promise,

18:59.806 --> 19:02.751
but I was too afraid,

19:02.775 --> 19:04.553
too ashamed.

19:04.577 --> 19:07.656
So why now?

19:07.680 --> 19:10.193
- When I read about
Cameron's accident,

19:10.217 --> 19:11.960
something just snapped.

19:11.984 --> 19:14.230
I had to come back here.

19:14.254 --> 19:16.832
I couldn't hide from
you any longer.

19:16.856 --> 19:20.636
- Allie's multimillion-dollar
inheritance had nothing to do with it?

19:20.660 --> 19:23.739
- I assure you, I have
all the money I need.

19:23.763 --> 19:26.475
- Do you have any kids?

19:26.499 --> 19:28.344
Other kids?

19:28.368 --> 19:30.479
- No. Robert didn't want

19:30.503 --> 19:32.439
any children. - Where is he?

19:34.574 --> 19:36.485
- We're not together
anymore, actually.

19:36.509 --> 19:38.411
Sadly, he's in prison.

19:40.613 --> 19:42.925
Let's just say his ambition got
the better of his judgement.

19:42.949 --> 19:46.529
- I'm surprised you'd share
that particular detail.

19:46.553 --> 19:48.864
- I told you, I have
nothing to hide.

19:48.888 --> 19:52.501
♪♪♪As far as you
and I go, Allison,

19:52.525 --> 19:56.339
I don't expect things to change overnight.
I really don't.

19:56.363 --> 19:58.298
I don't even expect
you to forgive me.

20:00.333 --> 20:03.712
But I would love the chance
to get to know you better.

20:03.736 --> 20:06.973
On your own terms of
course, in your own time.

20:11.411 --> 20:13.689
- Man: - I just left

20:13.713 --> 20:15.724
the house. The girl's
gonna be easy,

20:15.748 --> 20:17.828
but the sooner you get rid
of the lawyer, the better.

20:24.757 --> 20:26.869
For the "secretary"?

20:26.893 --> 20:30.038
- That's a little harsh.
- I'm just not sure I trust her.

20:30.062 --> 20:32.475
- You don't trust anyone.
- Come on, Allie,

20:32.499 --> 20:34.843
you have to admit. It's a little sketchy
she shows up right when Dad dies.

20:34.867 --> 20:37.480
- I don't know what to
think, but she is my mother.

20:37.504 --> 20:40.816
- On paper, sure, but 13 years
is a long freaking time.

20:40.840 --> 20:42.375
- Your sister has a point.

20:46.846 --> 20:49.024
- Oh! Gotta roll. Don't wait up.

20:49.048 --> 20:51.694
- Don't you think you should
take a night off from partying?

20:51.718 --> 20:53.662
- It's how I deal.

20:53.686 --> 20:55.455
- It's how you were
dealing before Dad died.

20:57.324 --> 20:59.868
- OK. Let's pretend
I'm the older sister

20:59.892 --> 21:02.805
and I tell you what to do.
- Girls, please.

21:02.829 --> 21:06.675
- OK, I'm sorry. Don't
worry, alright?

21:06.699 --> 21:08.511
I do, though. - I know.

21:08.535 --> 21:10.713
You're cool like that.

21:10.737 --> 21:14.541
♪♪♪

21:18.811 --> 21:22.325
- Yes, I'd like to order a dozen
pink carnations for delivery.

21:22.349 --> 21:25.093
Actually, make that 13.

21:25.117 --> 21:27.029
And I'd like the card to read,

21:27.053 --> 21:29.465
"My dear Allison,

21:29.489 --> 21:31.334
"I can't tell you how
much it meant for me

21:31.358 --> 21:33.436
"to see you today.

21:33.460 --> 21:36.872
"I only hope it's the first
of many more to come.

21:36.896 --> 21:39.775
Love, Jessica."

21:39.799 --> 21:42.902
♪♪♪

22:03.990 --> 22:06.902
- Followed the lawyer.
- And what do you have for me?

22:09.462 --> 22:12.441
Comes home to the wife and kids.
Doesn't even stop off for a drink.

22:12.465 --> 22:15.511
- Well, be patient,
you'll find his weakness.

22:18.605 --> 22:21.784
- I need something I can either hold
over his head or bury him with.

22:21.808 --> 22:25.454
I can just bury him for real.

22:25.478 --> 22:27.556
For now, let's
stick to the plan.

22:27.580 --> 22:30.526
Besides, I still need a little
more time to win over Allison.

22:30.550 --> 22:32.695
- And what if this guy's as
straight edge as he seems?

22:32.719 --> 22:35.731
- Hmm. Aaron said it himself,

22:35.755 --> 22:39.167
"Everyone's got
something to hide."

22:39.191 --> 22:41.970
I can't believe

22:41.994 --> 22:44.039
my dad had an affair
with this secretary.

22:44.063 --> 22:46.542
So cliché.

22:46.566 --> 22:48.777
- On the bright side, you did
get a great little sister

22:48.801 --> 22:50.913
out of it. - I just don't get

22:50.937 --> 22:52.948
what he would have
seen in that woman.

22:52.972 --> 22:54.950
- Yeah. Thing about couples
is nobody really knows

22:54.974 --> 22:57.376
what's going on between
them, except them.

23:00.747 --> 23:03.959
Taste.

23:03.983 --> 23:06.194
- It's good.

23:06.218 --> 23:08.997
♪♪♪

23:09.021 --> 23:11.634
- Tell me more about
your bio mom.

23:11.658 --> 23:14.136
- There's not really
much to tell.

23:14.160 --> 23:16.171
I'm seeing her again

23:16.195 --> 23:18.040
- Must be weird.

23:23.135 --> 23:26.449
- She did, like,
give birth to you.

23:26.473 --> 23:29.685
- I know, but me and my
parents were so close.

23:29.709 --> 23:31.954
- Mine are total
alien creatures.

23:31.978 --> 23:34.413
- At least, they're
still around.

23:41.187 --> 23:43.932
- It's OK. It's me.

23:43.956 --> 23:45.825
You get to say
anything you want.

23:58.004 --> 24:00.783
- Hi.

24:00.807 --> 24:03.719
- OK, well, I'm gonna
run a few errands

24:03.743 --> 24:05.688
and you text me when
you're ready to go.

24:05.712 --> 24:07.656
- Why don't you join us.

24:07.680 --> 24:09.658
- Oh! I don't, uh...

24:09.682 --> 24:11.660
- Please, I insist.

24:11.684 --> 24:13.762
I mean, we all should be
getting to know each other

24:13.786 --> 24:15.931
a little bit better, right?
- Yeah.

24:15.955 --> 24:18.224
- Sure. Sure, OK.
- Come with me.

24:20.593 --> 24:22.605
How are you?
- I'm good, thanks. How are you?

24:24.964 --> 24:27.275
- So, tell me, what are
some of your favourites?

24:27.299 --> 24:29.144
- Favourites?
- You know.

24:29.168 --> 24:30.913
Interests? Movies?

24:30.937 --> 24:34.583
- Well, I'm a pretty
big science geek.

24:34.607 --> 24:36.785
Ah. Like your father.

24:36.809 --> 24:38.687
- Yeah. He also got me

24:38.711 --> 24:40.556
into John Hughes' movies too.

24:40.580 --> 24:42.558
- Ah, I love those!

24:42.582 --> 24:44.593
What kind of music
do you listen to?

24:44.617 --> 24:47.820
- Uhh, I don't know. Anything
I can dance to, really.

24:49.922 --> 24:52.200
- Melinda, how long have you
been taking care of the girls?

24:52.224 --> 24:54.670
- Oh. Four years.

24:54.694 --> 24:56.639
I've been the housekeeper

24:56.663 --> 24:58.931
there about a year before
their mother passed.

25:02.034 --> 25:04.713
- Well, you must be
doing something right.

25:04.737 --> 25:07.249
Allison is quite the impressive
young lady, I must say.

25:07.273 --> 25:09.985
- So, where did you grow up?

25:10.009 --> 25:12.254
- Here.

25:12.278 --> 25:14.857
Well, not here, here.
South Philly.

25:14.881 --> 25:16.992
- Isn't that a rough
neighbourhood?

25:17.016 --> 25:20.863
- It is. But it taught me a lot.

25:20.887 --> 25:23.231
Made me strive for
something better.

25:23.255 --> 25:26.201
- So, any brothers or sisters?

25:26.225 --> 25:30.172
- No. I'm one of a kind.

25:30.196 --> 25:33.942
What about your sister? Where does
she go to school? - She doesn't.

25:33.966 --> 25:36.344
- Sydni took a gap year.

25:36.368 --> 25:39.081
Except for the gap
seems to be growing.

25:39.105 --> 25:41.917
- Aaah... Well, I'm sure
she'll find her way.

25:41.941 --> 25:43.852
- Mm-hmm.
- Do your parents

25:43.876 --> 25:46.021
still live here?

25:46.045 --> 25:49.616
- No. My mother died when I
was in high school. Overdose.

25:51.684 --> 25:55.254
- And your dad?
- He was never around.

25:57.389 --> 25:59.868
- I'm sorry.

25:59.892 --> 26:01.937
- I'm sorry about your dad.

26:01.961 --> 26:04.296
- I still can't
believe he's gone.

26:06.633 --> 26:08.644
I keep expecting him
to randomly text me

26:08.668 --> 26:10.613
or pick me up from school.

26:10.637 --> 26:13.281
- Yeah.

26:13.305 --> 26:16.318
Well, he sounds like he
was a pretty great dad.

26:16.342 --> 26:20.212
♪♪♪

26:22.281 --> 26:24.627
- Excuse me, ma'am. Excuse me.

26:24.651 --> 26:26.294
- Yes?

26:26.318 --> 26:29.297
- I'm afraid there's an
issue with your bill.

26:29.321 --> 26:31.634
- What issue? Why,
sign it to my room.

26:31.658 --> 26:34.002
- I'm not sure. Something to
do with your credit card.

26:34.026 --> 26:37.640
If you could just check in
with the front desk manager.

26:37.664 --> 26:39.799
- Yes, of course.
- Thank you.

26:43.936 --> 26:46.014
Wait, what do you
mean they seized

26:46.038 --> 26:48.751
the account? IT'S IN MY NAME!

26:48.775 --> 26:51.253
- BUT THAT'S MY MONEY!
- Hello?

26:51.277 --> 26:52.912
Hello?

26:55.682 --> 26:57.650
RRAAAH!

27:01.253 --> 27:03.265
- Ms. Calders?
- Yes?

27:03.289 --> 27:05.100
- It's Brian, the
front desk manager.

27:05.124 --> 27:08.170
♪♪♪

27:08.194 --> 27:10.096
- One minute, please!

27:14.967 --> 27:17.445
Come in.

27:17.469 --> 27:20.716
- Hi.
- Hi!

27:20.740 --> 27:22.885
- Uh, you were supposed
to come see me.

27:22.909 --> 27:24.720
- Oh, I was just about to.

27:24.744 --> 27:27.122
- Ah. Well, uh,

27:27.146 --> 27:29.758
for our long-term guests,
we periodically like

27:29.782 --> 27:32.160
to update the whole
amount on the card;

27:32.184 --> 27:35.130
I'm afraid yours
came back declined.

27:35.154 --> 27:37.299
- Oh!

27:37.323 --> 27:39.334
Well, I'm sure there's something

27:39.358 --> 27:41.303
we could do.

27:41.327 --> 27:43.906
What was your name again?
- Uh, it's Brian.

27:43.930 --> 27:46.709
- Ah, Brian. Yes, of course.

27:46.733 --> 27:50.212
You seem to take your job
very seriously, don't you?

27:50.236 --> 27:53.048
Uh, about the card...

27:53.072 --> 27:55.984
- Just relax.

27:56.008 --> 27:58.486
Relax. - No, no.

27:58.510 --> 28:01.289
No, no, no.

28:01.313 --> 28:03.992
Ah! - GET AWAY FROM ME!
GET OFF ME!

28:04.016 --> 28:06.194
HELP! - What the hell?!

28:06.218 --> 28:09.464
- Now listen here, Brian. You're
gonna write off that bill

28:09.488 --> 28:11.499
or I'm gonna call the police
and tell them you just tried

28:11.523 --> 28:13.468
to rape me.
- What? I didn't even touch you!

28:13.492 --> 28:16.204
- Let's not quibble about the details.
You know how thin

28:16.228 --> 28:18.240
these walls are, and your
guests just heard me screaming.

28:18.264 --> 28:20.342
- You're out of your mind.

28:20.366 --> 28:24.446
- Insulting me isn't helping.
GET OFF ME!

28:24.470 --> 28:27.783
Maybe I'll just call them right now.
- Just wait.

28:27.807 --> 28:30.342
Alright. Alright. OK.

28:32.178 --> 28:35.081
- Now get the hell out of here.

28:54.333 --> 28:57.269
♪♪♪

29:00.807 --> 29:03.910
How much for these?

29:11.183 --> 29:13.561
- Three grand, I can give you.

29:13.585 --> 29:15.798
- What?! They're worth
ten times that much.

29:15.822 --> 29:18.200
- They're only worth what
someone's willing to pay.

29:18.224 --> 29:20.402
- I don't need a lesson in economics.
I came here

29:20.426 --> 29:22.237
because I was told
you were reasonable.

29:22.261 --> 29:24.907
- I'll tell you what,

29:24.931 --> 29:28.576
I'll give you 3500,
but no reserve.

29:28.600 --> 29:31.013
I find a buyer for these
and they're gone.

29:31.037 --> 29:33.015
- Well, don't worry,
I won't be back.

29:33.039 --> 29:35.207
♪♪♪

29:42.915 --> 29:45.027
Are you kidding me?!

29:45.051 --> 29:47.162
Hey! Hey!

29:47.186 --> 29:49.865
You forgot something!

29:49.889 --> 29:52.258
Here!

30:02.501 --> 30:04.546
- There's only the
one bedroom...

30:04.570 --> 30:08.083
but I'm sure we can
figure something out.

30:08.107 --> 30:10.018
- I appreciate you
letting me stay.

30:10.042 --> 30:12.187
Hopefully won't be for too long.

30:12.211 --> 30:15.390
Those feds had no right to take my money.
- Yeah, well,

30:15.414 --> 30:17.549
the feds don't need rights.
They're feds.

30:21.921 --> 30:24.032
- I hate to ask,

30:24.056 --> 30:26.034
but I'm gonna need
to borrow some cash.

30:26.058 --> 30:29.471
- Not a problem. I'll
just put it on your tab.

30:29.495 --> 30:32.307
With interests.

30:32.331 --> 30:34.376
- Where are we with Aaron?

30:34.400 --> 30:36.444
- Well, that's where
I'm going right now.

30:36.468 --> 30:39.247
- Oh?
- Yeah.

30:39.271 --> 30:41.151
I got a little surprise
planned for him tonight.

31:02.194 --> 31:04.206
- Excuse me.
- Yes?

31:04.230 --> 31:06.274
- I'm sorry. I saw you come in

31:06.298 --> 31:08.410
and I just had to meet you.

31:08.434 --> 31:11.679
- OK.
- I never do anything like this,

31:11.703 --> 31:14.549
but there was just
something about you.

31:14.573 --> 31:18.220
- Listen, I'm sorry,
but I'm married.

31:18.244 --> 31:21.413
Flattered but married.
- We can still have drinks.

31:23.449 --> 31:26.194
- Actually, we can't.
We really can't.

31:26.218 --> 31:29.155
♪♪♪

31:44.470 --> 31:46.714
- Do you know anyone
good with computers?

31:46.738 --> 31:50.118
- Sure. Can't really
steal much these days

31:50.142 --> 31:53.588
without technical support.
- Someone you can trust?

31:53.612 --> 31:56.482
- Well, some of my best
relationships started in prison.

31:58.384 --> 32:00.462
Relax. He got
popped for assault.

32:00.486 --> 32:02.664
As a hacker, he's
still undefeated.

32:02.688 --> 32:05.567
Why? What do you got in mind?

32:05.591 --> 32:08.403
- Well, if Aaron really
has nothing to hide,

32:08.427 --> 32:12.107
then I guess we'll just
have to give him something.

32:14.266 --> 32:18.204
♪♪♪

32:33.619 --> 32:36.522
♪♪♪

32:51.337 --> 32:54.473
♪♪♪

33:17.529 --> 33:19.598
- And...

33:21.567 --> 33:24.512
We're in.

33:24.536 --> 33:27.249
- How did you get
past that password?

33:27.273 --> 33:30.318
- A magician never
shares his secrets.

33:30.342 --> 33:32.687
- Oh, Aaron,

33:32.711 --> 33:35.057
you have been

33:35.081 --> 33:37.459
a bad, bad boy.

33:40.486 --> 33:42.497
- This is weird.

33:42.521 --> 33:45.133
- I think it's amazing.

33:45.157 --> 33:47.602
- Not the food. This,
the whole, like,

33:47.626 --> 33:49.604
family-dinner thing.

33:49.628 --> 33:51.530
Ahem!

33:54.300 --> 33:57.212
- I think I want to
go back to school.

33:57.236 --> 33:59.614
- Oh, that's great!

33:59.638 --> 34:01.816
- I just want to start
being normal again.

34:01.840 --> 34:03.518
- Of course you do.
And you will.

34:06.278 --> 34:09.591
- Excuse me, but I gotta go.
- Oh! You've been out

34:09.614 --> 34:11.793
almost every night this week.

34:11.817 --> 34:14.329
- Thanks for dinner. Allie, if
you need me, just call me, OK?

34:19.358 --> 34:21.335
- She has a new boyfriend.

34:21.360 --> 34:23.205
Tommy.

34:23.228 --> 34:26.608
- Have you met him yet?
- No.

34:26.632 --> 34:29.610
They don't usually last
long enough for me to.

34:29.635 --> 34:31.413
- Everyone deals with
grief differently.

34:31.437 --> 34:34.706
- How did you deal with
it when your mom died?

34:36.342 --> 34:38.853
- Not very well.

34:38.877 --> 34:40.888
I was pretty self-destructive.

34:40.911 --> 34:42.824
Stayed that way for a long time.

34:42.848 --> 34:45.592
- What changed?

34:45.617 --> 34:48.730
- Having you.

34:48.754 --> 34:51.766
Then losing you.

34:51.790 --> 34:54.636
After that, something
just clicked.

34:54.659 --> 34:56.594
I just started making
better choices.

35:03.402 --> 35:05.380
You alright?

35:05.404 --> 35:07.515
Yeah.

35:07.539 --> 35:09.441
- You're just somewhere else.

35:11.310 --> 35:13.521
- I was just thinking
about Allie.

35:13.545 --> 35:15.657
Things are pretty crazy
for her right now.

35:15.681 --> 35:19.227
- For you too. I mean,
losing your dad,

35:19.251 --> 35:21.363
to take care of
your little sister;

35:21.387 --> 35:24.166
it's gotta be hard.

35:24.190 --> 35:27.235
- Yeah.

35:27.259 --> 35:29.395
But I haven't really been
there for her like I should.

35:32.264 --> 35:34.576
She's got Melinda though.

35:34.600 --> 35:38.246
And her new mom of course.

35:38.270 --> 35:40.715
- You don't like
her, the mother?

35:40.739 --> 35:42.384
- Hell no!

35:42.408 --> 35:46.654
But Allie does, so...

35:46.678 --> 35:48.580
I have to respect that.

35:55.521 --> 35:57.532
- Aaron Martin?
- How can I help you?

35:57.556 --> 36:00.202
- Detective Peters.
We have a warrant

36:00.226 --> 36:02.837
to search your home and office.
- Search for what exactly?

36:04.963 --> 36:08.243
You kidding me? - No, I'm not.

36:08.267 --> 36:10.678
- Hey.

36:10.702 --> 36:12.538
Hey!

36:15.607 --> 36:17.819
- I thought you wanted to
keep things professional.

36:17.843 --> 36:20.888
- You're not
suggesting I pay you?

36:20.912 --> 36:23.591
- Mm-mm.

36:23.615 --> 36:25.517
What are you doing?

36:27.653 --> 36:31.189
- One down, one to go.

36:35.261 --> 36:36.671
- The housekeeper?

36:36.695 --> 36:39.574
- I no longer require
her services.

36:39.598 --> 36:42.577
- How do you want to handle it?

36:42.601 --> 36:44.641
- Doesn't she seem like the
most wonderful daughter?

37:02.321 --> 37:04.399
- Thanks for the spa day.

37:04.423 --> 37:07.001
- A woman always needs
to treat herself.

37:07.025 --> 37:09.271
And you have to look your best
if you're going back to school.

37:09.295 --> 37:11.473
- True.

37:11.497 --> 37:14.409
- You're a strong,
young woman, Allison.

37:14.433 --> 37:16.578
You got it pretty rough,
but you've come through it

37:16.602 --> 37:18.580
with poise and grace.

37:18.604 --> 37:20.848
- Like you!
- Yeah? I'm glad

37:20.872 --> 37:23.285
you think so. By the way,

37:23.309 --> 37:25.687
I wanted you to be
the first to know

37:25.711 --> 37:27.622
I've decided to stay
here in Philly.

37:27.646 --> 37:29.591
- That's great!
- Yeah.

37:29.615 --> 37:31.759
It's...

37:31.783 --> 37:33.761
home.

37:33.785 --> 37:36.688
♪♪♪

37:54.540 --> 37:56.442
♪♪♪

38:13.725 --> 38:16.662
♪♪♪

38:27.038 --> 38:30.418
- What do you want?

38:30.442 --> 38:33.311
My purse is over there.

38:35.381 --> 38:38.016
Ugh!

38:39.685 --> 38:42.721
♪♪♪

39:01.540 --> 39:03.851
- One of the city's most

39:03.875 --> 39:05.953
respected attorneys,
Aaron Martin,

39:05.977 --> 39:08.055
was arrested today
for possession

39:08.079 --> 39:10.525
of child pornography.

39:10.549 --> 39:14.128
Police allege that Martin
accessed a website being tracked

39:14.152 --> 39:16.130
by the Department's
Special Victims Unit.

39:16.154 --> 39:18.099
This was part of a larger

39:18.123 --> 39:20.034
ongoing investigation
we reported on

39:20.058 --> 39:22.837
earlier this month.
The 46 year old,

39:22.861 --> 39:25.106
who is married and has
a 10-year-old son,

39:25.130 --> 39:27.475
has declined to comment.
- I can't believe

39:27.499 --> 39:30.645
this is happening.
- This has to be a mistake.

39:30.669 --> 39:32.947
- I certainly hope so.
- No.

39:32.971 --> 39:36.651
There's no way. I'm telling you,
Aaron is the sweetest guy alive.

39:36.675 --> 39:38.920
- So maybe he got hacked.

39:38.944 --> 39:41.589
- Why would anyone
do that to him?

39:41.613 --> 39:43.691
- He is a lawyer;

39:43.715 --> 39:45.560
he must have made a few
enemies along the way.

39:55.060 --> 39:56.738
- Hey, Mr. Kelton.
- Hey.

39:56.762 --> 39:58.640
- Adrian Kelton. I'm one
of the partners here.

39:58.664 --> 40:00.975
- Jessica. I'm Allison's mother.
- Ah, yes.

40:00.999 --> 40:02.868
Please have a seat.

40:08.173 --> 40:10.485
Aaron's out on bail,

40:10.509 --> 40:12.454
but we think it best that
I take over as executor.

40:12.478 --> 40:14.722
At least until his
case goes to trial.

40:14.746 --> 40:16.924
- He's innocent, isn't he?

40:16.948 --> 40:20.161
- Of course he is, Allie.
- I believe he is too.

40:20.185 --> 40:22.029
But proving it is
gonna be a challenge.

40:22.053 --> 40:24.098
- You're taking care

40:24.122 --> 40:26.601
of the girls' finances,
which is great,

40:26.625 --> 40:28.636
but who's gonna
take care of them?

40:28.660 --> 40:31.038
- How do you mean?
- Well, Aaron's also

40:31.062 --> 40:33.074
their legal guardian,
but now the housekeeper

40:33.098 --> 40:36.611
just had to leave suddenly.
Some sort of family emergency.

40:36.635 --> 40:39.246
- Her mother was robbed
and beaten pretty badly.

40:39.270 --> 40:42.550
- Well, if it's alright with you
girls, I'd love to help out.

40:42.574 --> 40:44.752
- Help out

40:44.776 --> 40:46.488
how?

40:46.512 --> 40:48.923
- I was thinking I
could stay with you,

40:48.947 --> 40:51.693
help take care of the house.
You know, just until

40:51.717 --> 40:54.085
things work themselves out.
- That would be great!

40:56.655 --> 41:00.134
- Sydni, is that
alright with you?

41:00.158 --> 41:01.727
- Hmm...

41:05.964 --> 41:08.543
Sure.

41:08.567 --> 41:10.168
Yeah, I guess.

41:13.104 --> 41:16.141
♪♪♪

41:20.946 --> 41:23.081
- Home, sweet home.

41:27.686 --> 41:29.664
- There's the bathroom,

41:29.688 --> 41:32.099
some towels. Even a robe.

41:32.123 --> 41:33.992
- Everything a girl needs.

41:36.728 --> 41:38.773
Where is your sister?

41:38.797 --> 41:41.576
- She's been staying
with Tommy a lot.

41:41.600 --> 41:43.268
I'm actually kind of worried.

41:45.136 --> 41:47.549
- You don't like him?
- I don't like

41:47.573 --> 41:50.251
all the drinking and
the other stuff.

41:50.275 --> 41:53.688
- Drugs?

41:53.712 --> 41:56.323
- You know she got accepted
to an art school in New York?

41:56.347 --> 42:00.127
But ever since Mom
died, she's been...

42:00.151 --> 42:02.564
I don't even know.

42:02.588 --> 42:05.032
Like, she's lost.

42:05.056 --> 42:08.570
- Your sister's a lot
like I was at her age.

42:08.594 --> 42:11.338
- Maybe you can help her.

42:11.362 --> 42:14.299
- Maybe, but she has
to want the help.

42:17.335 --> 42:19.204
- I'm really glad you're here.

42:21.239 --> 42:23.317
- Me too.

42:38.757 --> 42:41.693
♪♪♪

42:52.904 --> 42:55.974
♪♪♪

43:14.693 --> 43:17.629
♪♪♪

43:31.076 --> 43:34.045
♪♪♪

43:35.914 --> 43:38.817
- I'm not really
feeling school today.

43:40.418 --> 43:42.997
- It'll be alright.

43:43.021 --> 43:46.768
- I just keep
thinking about Aaron.

43:46.792 --> 43:48.836
- Aaron's an excellent lawyer;

43:48.860 --> 43:50.872
if he is innocent, he'll
be able to prove it.

43:50.896 --> 43:54.108
- I hope so.

43:54.132 --> 43:56.844
- I wish the circumstances
were different, but we're

43:56.868 --> 43:59.313
together now, and I'm gonna
sure you have the best life

43:59.337 --> 44:01.783
you could possibly have.

44:01.807 --> 44:04.075
- Thanks.

44:06.144 --> 44:08.189
- It means the world to me

44:08.213 --> 44:10.381
that you don't believe.
- Not for a second.

44:18.323 --> 44:20.467
- Reporters keep
coming by the house.

44:20.491 --> 44:23.795
And I had to send the family
to stay with her parents.

44:26.364 --> 44:28.743
- Have you thought about who
might have done this to you?

44:28.767 --> 44:31.278
- It's all I've been
thinking about.

44:31.302 --> 44:34.081
- Maybe someone you
sued or something?

44:34.105 --> 44:37.151
- Definitely cost people some
serious money in my day,

44:37.175 --> 44:39.655
but it's been years since I've
been involved in any litigation.

44:42.748 --> 44:45.359
- Why else would someone
do something so vile?

44:45.383 --> 44:47.394
- They'd have to have
something to gain.

44:47.418 --> 44:49.054
- Like what?
- Well...

44:51.289 --> 44:53.835
if I was convicted, I could no
longer serve as Allison's guardian.

44:53.859 --> 44:56.871
- You think Jessica did this?
- I don't know.

44:56.895 --> 44:59.006
♪♪♪

44:59.030 --> 45:01.475
I am the one thing standing
between her and Allison's money.

45:01.499 --> 45:06.147
- I thought she has money.
- She does, but not what she's used to.

45:06.171 --> 45:08.482
Nothing compared to what your
sister could provide her.

45:08.506 --> 45:11.118
- Why didn't you
tell us this before?

45:11.142 --> 45:14.856
- I don't know. I couldn't
be sure of her motives.

45:14.880 --> 45:17.158
I didn't want to put the
idea in Allison's head

45:17.182 --> 45:20.194
in case I was wrong.

45:20.218 --> 45:22.329
- Jessica doesn't
really strike me

45:22.353 --> 45:25.290
as very tech savvy. - No.

45:27.192 --> 45:29.470
No.

45:29.494 --> 45:31.362
But she could have had help.

45:33.999 --> 45:36.768
♪♪♪

45:46.812 --> 45:48.522
- Thought you weren't
coming back.

45:48.546 --> 45:50.958
- Just give me my money.

45:57.422 --> 45:59.500
Is not convinced Aaron's guilty.

45:59.524 --> 46:01.335
- Don't worry about Sydni.
Just stick to the plan.

46:01.359 --> 46:04.205
- When are you gonna
learn to trust me?

46:04.229 --> 46:06.297
- The only thing I
trust is money.

46:09.167 --> 46:11.169
- There you go. 3200.

46:17.042 --> 46:19.878
♪♪♪

46:40.298 --> 46:43.134
♪♪♪

46:45.403 --> 46:48.306
- Bummer.

47:03.454 --> 47:06.324
♪♪♪

47:46.064 --> 47:49.567
♪♪♪

47:55.306 --> 47:57.985
Oh, hey! - Sydni?

47:58.009 --> 48:00.587
- I was just heading out.

48:00.611 --> 48:02.957
- I'm taking your sister
shopping a little later;

48:02.981 --> 48:04.658
if you care to join, my treat.
- Oh, thanks,

48:04.682 --> 48:06.527
but I have plans
with my boyfriend.

48:06.551 --> 48:08.495
- Tommy, right?

48:08.519 --> 48:11.565
You should bring him by
sometime; I'd love to meet him.

48:11.589 --> 48:13.424
- Yeah, sure.

48:16.261 --> 48:20.265
♪♪♪

49:02.640 --> 49:05.243
- Someone's been sticking their
nose where it doesn't belong.

49:12.583 --> 49:15.062
Something wrong with this
woman from the start.

49:15.086 --> 49:18.099
- Yeah, does sound pretty crazy.
- And Aaron

49:18.123 --> 49:20.167
is the only one who's known
her since back in the day.

49:20.191 --> 49:22.303
So now that he's out of the
way, she can just keep

49:22.327 --> 49:24.305
telling Allie that she's
become this wonderful person.

49:24.329 --> 49:28.042
- I guess, but your
sister is still a kid;

49:28.066 --> 49:29.776
wouldn't her money be in
a trust or something?

49:29.800 --> 49:32.179
- Yeah, but she's
willing to wait.

49:32.203 --> 49:34.081
Wouldn't you be for 40 million?

49:34.105 --> 49:37.218
- I know.

49:37.242 --> 49:39.486
- Then, Melinda's
mother gets attacked,

49:39.510 --> 49:41.688
and Melinda moves out, and
Jessica moves right in.

49:41.712 --> 49:43.457
- Wait.

49:43.481 --> 49:45.492
You're not saying she's
behind that too?

49:45.516 --> 49:47.761
- You have to admit: it's a
pretty damn big coincidence.

49:47.785 --> 49:49.530
- If you really
think you're right

49:49.554 --> 49:52.766
about any of this, then
we should go to the cops.

49:52.790 --> 49:54.768
- Yeah.

49:54.792 --> 49:56.770
You're right.

50:05.170 --> 50:07.314
Hey, Aunt Monica.

50:07.338 --> 50:09.750
I'm alright.

50:11.776 --> 50:14.455
- Yeah. But I talked
to her the other day,

50:14.479 --> 50:16.523
and her mom is doing
a lot better.

50:19.350 --> 50:20.727
- Jessica, yeah.

50:24.089 --> 50:26.300
- Well, I've got some good news.

50:26.324 --> 50:29.203
- Really?

50:29.227 --> 50:30.788
- [He just has to wind
down a project he's

50:30.800 --> 50:32.373
[working on. The house
is already up for sale.]

50:32.397 --> 50:34.575
That's great!

50:34.599 --> 50:36.677
- The same.

50:36.701 --> 50:38.612
Child:

50:38.636 --> 50:40.647
You did?

50:40.671 --> 50:43.284
Grandpa help you with that?

50:50.248 --> 50:52.526
Now, I want you to give

50:52.550 --> 50:54.528
Mom a big kiss for me, OK?

50:57.188 --> 50:59.533
I miss you too.

50:59.557 --> 51:01.668
- Bye.

51:01.692 --> 51:03.770
♪♪♪

51:20.878 --> 51:23.814
♪♪♪

51:33.258 --> 51:35.736
To my wife

51:35.760 --> 51:37.662
and son.

51:40.198 --> 51:42.576
You deserved

51:42.600 --> 51:46.713
so much more.

51:46.737 --> 51:49.740
♪♪♪

52:06.491 --> 52:08.835
Just so you know,
this isn't personal.

52:08.859 --> 52:10.804
It's just business.

52:23.241 --> 52:24.509
- Thanks.

52:26.544 --> 52:28.789
- It's getting late.
- Well, I would have done it

52:28.813 --> 52:31.558
earlier, but someone insisted
on dinner and a movie.

52:36.721 --> 52:38.665
- Hello?
- Man:

52:38.689 --> 52:41.368
♪♪♪- Yes?

52:41.392 --> 52:42.869
- See? Told you.

52:42.893 --> 52:45.539
Worth every penny. Maybe more.

52:45.563 --> 52:48.342
- Thank you, but I'm
not interested.

52:49.967 --> 52:53.238
- Yes, I'm sure. Thank you.

52:55.506 --> 52:59.720
- I hate telemarketers.
- They can be such a nuisance.

53:01.679 --> 53:04.558
- Peters.
- Woman:

53:04.582 --> 53:06.727
Yeah?

53:09.254 --> 53:11.889
- OK. Be right there.

53:15.660 --> 53:17.938
- So, you're telling me
that your sister's mother

53:17.962 --> 53:20.574
framed Mr. Martin?

53:20.598 --> 53:22.509
- I can't prove it,
but I'm pretty sure

53:22.533 --> 53:24.445
she's after Allie's inheritance.

53:24.469 --> 53:26.580
And I know Aaron;

53:26.604 --> 53:28.439
he would never do what
he's been accused of.

53:31.041 --> 53:34.321
- How long have you known him?
- My entire life.

53:34.345 --> 53:36.381
He was my dad's closest friend.

53:38.449 --> 53:40.461
I hate to tell you this,

53:40.485 --> 53:42.763
but Mr. Martin is dead.

53:42.787 --> 53:45.599
♪♪♪

53:45.623 --> 53:47.768
- What?!

53:47.792 --> 53:51.438
How?

53:51.462 --> 53:53.474
- It's too early
for me to comment,

53:53.498 --> 53:55.300
but it would appear
he took his own life.

53:56.967 --> 53:58.945
- No.

53:58.969 --> 54:01.948
No, it... There's no way.

54:01.972 --> 54:04.241
Aaron would never...

54:05.810 --> 54:08.613
- Alright. Let me
look into this.

54:10.748 --> 54:13.951
Take care of yourself.

54:23.694 --> 54:25.906
- Thanks for the ride.
- Wait!

54:25.930 --> 54:29.376
- Just leave me alone!
- Allie, we have known

54:29.400 --> 54:31.812
Aaron forever. I just talked
to him yesterday. He was ready

54:31.836 --> 54:33.914
to fight this thing.
- Apparently not.

54:33.938 --> 54:37.618
- You have to admit, there's
at least a possibility.

54:37.642 --> 54:39.853
- Jessica did not kill Aaron.
She was with me

54:39.877 --> 54:41.922
all night. - Then, she must have

54:41.946 --> 54:44.325
someone helping her.
- Do you even know how insane

54:44.349 --> 54:46.427
you sound right now?
- Allie, listen to me.

54:46.451 --> 54:48.028
- No! Jessica's been

54:48.052 --> 54:50.531
nothing but supportive
ever since she got here,

54:50.555 --> 54:53.934
and she hasn't asked for a thing in return.
- She asked to live with us!

54:53.958 --> 54:55.869
- I don't know what's
going on with you, Syd,

54:55.893 --> 54:58.805
but you seriously
need some help.

54:58.829 --> 55:00.407
- Allie!

55:18.516 --> 55:21.352
♪♪♪

55:27.492 --> 55:30.737
- I'm really sorry, babe.

55:30.761 --> 55:32.739
It had to have been Jessica.

55:32.763 --> 55:35.642
- Framing somebody is
one thing, but murder?

55:37.702 --> 55:39.980
- It's the only thing
that makes sense.

55:40.004 --> 55:41.939
- None of this makes sense.

55:44.108 --> 55:46.119
- Aaron would have
fought those charges.

55:46.143 --> 55:49.390
And he would have won. She
must have known that.

55:49.414 --> 55:51.494
- It's a pretty elaborate
way to get rid of somebody.

55:55.185 --> 55:57.087
- Oh, my God!

56:04.829 --> 56:07.932
♪♪♪

56:19.910 --> 56:21.955
- OK, what's it gonna be?

56:21.979 --> 56:24.124
Breakfast Club or
Pretty In Pink?

56:24.148 --> 56:26.884
- I don't think I'm really
feeling movie night tonight.

56:30.521 --> 56:32.966
- What happened to Aaron
was tragic, I know,

56:32.990 --> 56:35.035
but we can't let ourselves
be dragged down.

56:35.059 --> 56:37.037
Remember what your
father used to say,

56:37.061 --> 56:39.039
"Always look at
the bright side."

56:39.063 --> 56:41.975
- I'm not really
seeing one right now.

56:41.999 --> 56:44.911
- I know. But you
will soon, I promise.

56:44.935 --> 56:46.947
Besides, you've got a
birthday coming up.

56:46.971 --> 56:48.949
Maybe we could start
planning your celebration?

56:48.973 --> 56:51.117
- Um, maybe.
- Doesn't have to be

56:51.141 --> 56:54.721
a big thing. We could invite
some friends from school,

56:54.745 --> 56:57.991
Erica, your sister.

56:58.015 --> 57:01.795
- Sydni's got her own
problems right now.

57:01.819 --> 57:03.764
- Yeah, she hasn't been
around very much lately.

57:03.788 --> 57:05.766
Is everything OK?

57:05.790 --> 57:08.134
- I don't know.

57:08.158 --> 57:10.904
- Where is she staying?
- At Tommy's.

57:10.928 --> 57:13.474
- Oh.

57:13.498 --> 57:15.476
Well, one thing I know for sure,

57:15.500 --> 57:17.978
your sister loves you very much.

57:18.002 --> 57:20.881
She's gonna try her very best
to be at your party, I'm sure.

57:20.905 --> 57:22.940
Right?

57:26.777 --> 57:29.614
♪♪♪

57:46.096 --> 57:48.933
♪♪♪

58:03.581 --> 58:05.950
♪♪♪

58:27.171 --> 58:30.107
♪♪♪

58:41.318 --> 58:44.221
♪♪♪

58:57.234 --> 58:59.604
♪♪♪

59:19.123 --> 59:21.992
- Excuse me?
- Office is up front.

59:23.794 --> 59:25.129
- Mr. Thomas?

59:27.297 --> 59:30.110
- Who are you?
- My name's Sydni.

59:30.134 --> 59:31.969
Cameron Timmons was my father.

59:33.804 --> 59:35.139
- I'm sorry to hear that.

59:37.241 --> 59:39.953
- I just wanted to know...
- Want to know what everyone

59:39.977 --> 59:42.057
else wants to know, but
really, nobody wants to know.

59:44.314 --> 59:47.928
- The report said that...
- I know what the report said.

59:47.952 --> 59:49.796
The report said I
didn't do my job.

59:49.820 --> 59:52.265
The report said I
failed to inspect

59:52.289 --> 59:54.200
the fuel lines. The
same fuel lines

59:54.224 --> 59:56.064
I've been inspecting for
damn near seven years.

59:58.128 --> 01:00:01.074
- So, then what really happened?

01:00:01.098 --> 01:00:03.309
- All I know is I
did the preflight

01:00:03.333 --> 01:00:05.411
on that plane, as always,

01:00:05.435 --> 01:00:07.681
and she was 100%.

01:00:07.705 --> 01:00:10.416
- So you're saying someone
tampered with it?

01:00:10.440 --> 01:00:13.143
- Unless you believe in
paranormal activity of some kind.

01:00:15.680 --> 01:00:17.824
- Then why wasn't there
an investigation?

01:00:17.848 --> 01:00:21.728
♪♪♪

01:00:21.752 --> 01:00:24.731
- There was.

01:00:24.755 --> 01:00:27.167
They couldn't find anything
conclusive in the wreckage,

01:00:27.191 --> 01:00:29.269
and, uh, apparently

01:00:29.293 --> 01:00:31.705
nobody had anything to
gain financially speaking.

01:00:31.729 --> 01:00:34.675
It was just

01:00:34.699 --> 01:00:36.834
cleaner and easier
to put it all on me.

01:00:39.069 --> 01:00:42.148
- What if someone did
have something to gain?

01:00:42.172 --> 01:00:44.050
- Well, you could try

01:00:44.074 --> 01:00:46.687
telling the cops.

01:00:46.711 --> 01:00:48.946
I sure wouldn't mind
getting my job back.

01:00:53.851 --> 01:00:56.096
- What? So the sister
is the problem now?

01:00:56.120 --> 01:00:58.255
- Not a problem, just
an inconvenience.

01:01:00.490 --> 01:01:03.136
She's been calling this
number a lot lately.

01:01:03.160 --> 01:01:05.271
Must be one of her boyfriends.
Tommy something.

01:01:05.295 --> 01:01:08.742
♪♪♪

01:01:08.766 --> 01:01:11.411
Can you get me an address?

01:01:11.435 --> 01:01:14.748
- Yeah, I can do more than that.
- It's alright. I'll take care of her.

01:01:14.772 --> 01:01:17.150
- Hey, why don't you try
taking care of me first.

01:01:17.174 --> 01:01:19.143
OK.

01:01:24.448 --> 01:01:27.894
- Come on, Jessica! I spend
more than this in a night out.

01:01:27.918 --> 01:01:30.320
- It's all I can
get at the moment.

01:01:35.793 --> 01:01:38.371
- So you came to me

01:01:38.395 --> 01:01:41.908
because you couldn't do
what needed to be done.

01:01:41.932 --> 01:01:44.778
You wanted your baby daddy
dead; now he's dead.

01:01:44.802 --> 01:01:47.180
You wanted his lawyer dead;
well, he's dead too.

01:01:47.204 --> 01:01:49.515
- Cole, please...
- You see?

01:01:49.539 --> 01:01:53.486
What you and I have here,
it's like a marriage. Mhm?

01:01:53.510 --> 01:01:56.089
"For richer or for poorer

01:01:56.113 --> 01:01:58.458
'til death do us part."

01:01:58.482 --> 01:02:01.418
♪♪♪

01:02:10.928 --> 01:02:12.505
- Oh! And that guy she was with,

01:02:12.529 --> 01:02:14.808
his name's Cole Flannery.

01:02:14.832 --> 01:02:16.977
Did, like, three years in
prison for money laundering.

01:02:17.001 --> 01:02:18.945
- And you're sure that's
the same guy you saw

01:02:18.969 --> 01:02:21.138
outside my house? - Pretty sure.

01:02:23.273 --> 01:02:26.286
- Now, do you think I'm crazy?

01:02:26.310 --> 01:02:28.321
- We still can't
prove any of this.

01:02:28.345 --> 01:02:31.191
- Well, we're a hell of a lot
closer than we were before.

01:02:31.215 --> 01:02:33.126
Now maybe that detective
will believe me.

01:02:33.150 --> 01:02:35.385
Here, hand me my phone.

01:02:38.355 --> 01:02:41.835
♪♪♪

01:02:41.859 --> 01:02:44.304
- Can I offer you anything,
Detective Peters?

01:02:44.328 --> 01:02:46.472
- No, thank you. I
don't want to take up

01:02:46.496 --> 01:02:48.809
too much of your time.
- Whatever we can do to help.

01:02:48.833 --> 01:02:51.812
Please. - Maybe your daughter

01:02:51.836 --> 01:02:54.414
has some homework to do.
- Anything you have to say,

01:02:54.438 --> 01:02:57.942
Allison should hear. I
have no secrets from her.

01:03:00.477 --> 01:03:02.555
- Can you tell me where you were

01:03:02.579 --> 01:03:04.991
on the night of Aaron
Martin's death?

01:03:05.015 --> 01:03:07.451
- Of course. I was right here
at the house with Allison.

01:03:09.854 --> 01:03:11.965
- How do you know Cole Flannery?

01:03:11.989 --> 01:03:14.434
♪♪♪- We dated back
in high school.

01:03:14.458 --> 01:03:17.570
- And now?
- When I came to town,

01:03:17.594 --> 01:03:20.306
I needed a car. I'd heard
he was in the car business.

01:03:20.330 --> 01:03:22.366
- Among other things.

01:03:24.434 --> 01:03:26.236
Anything more I should know?

01:03:29.073 --> 01:03:32.085
- He gave me a good deal.
What's all this about?

01:03:32.109 --> 01:03:34.287
- We're looking

01:03:34.311 --> 01:03:37.557
at Mr. Flannery in a number
of felony investigations.

01:03:37.581 --> 01:03:41.027
- Oh. I had no idea.

01:03:41.051 --> 01:03:43.329
Seemed like such a gentleman.

01:03:43.353 --> 01:03:45.899
- Hmm. Far from it.

01:03:45.923 --> 01:03:48.368
- Well, I suppose I should

01:03:48.392 --> 01:03:51.171
keep my distance then
and return the car.

01:03:51.195 --> 01:03:53.874
- You can use Dad's car.

01:03:53.898 --> 01:03:55.942
It's just sitting there.

01:03:55.966 --> 01:03:58.068
- That's very sweet. Thank you.

01:04:00.270 --> 01:04:02.215
Is there anything else,
Detective Peters?

01:04:02.239 --> 01:04:04.184
I really should
get dinner going.

01:04:04.208 --> 01:04:06.019
- No. We're good for now.

01:04:06.043 --> 01:04:08.443
- Great. If there's anything
else, you know where to find me.

01:04:13.383 --> 01:04:16.286
♪♪♪

01:04:30.467 --> 01:04:33.370
♪♪♪

01:04:53.523 --> 01:04:56.336
- Hey, Jessica.
- Hey!

01:04:56.360 --> 01:04:58.404
I'll just finish my coffee, and
then I'll drive you to school.

01:04:58.428 --> 01:05:00.640
- Don't worry about it;
Syd's picking me up.

01:05:00.664 --> 01:05:02.592
- She is? - Yeah, she texted me

01:05:02.604 --> 01:05:04.544
last night, said
she wants to talk.

01:05:04.568 --> 01:05:08.172
- Oh. Well, that's
probably a good thing.

01:05:10.507 --> 01:05:14.044
♪♪♪

01:05:29.526 --> 01:05:31.704
- Police! Hands where
I can see 'em!

01:05:31.728 --> 01:05:34.040
- What did I do?
- You tell me.

01:05:34.064 --> 01:05:36.109
Is there anything in here
I need to worry about?

01:05:36.133 --> 01:05:39.436
- No! What do you mean? ♪♪♪

01:05:46.176 --> 01:05:48.554
- That's what I mean.
- That's not mine.

01:05:48.578 --> 01:05:50.623
- Turn around!
- Are you kidding me!

01:05:50.647 --> 01:05:53.393
- You're under arrest.
- What?!

01:05:53.417 --> 01:05:55.261
Oh, my God.

01:05:55.285 --> 01:05:57.030
This is a mistake.

01:05:57.054 --> 01:05:59.299
Oh. My. God.

01:05:59.323 --> 01:06:02.168
- Now you're telling me
that she framed you too?

01:06:02.192 --> 01:06:03.603
- She must have just
grabbed my spare

01:06:03.615 --> 01:06:05.038
keys from the house!
- Oh yeah, yeah.

01:06:05.062 --> 01:06:07.740
And I bet you've never
done drugs either.

01:06:07.764 --> 01:06:09.609
- I'm no angel, alright?
I've probably

01:06:09.633 --> 01:06:11.744
partied more than a...

01:06:11.768 --> 01:06:14.080
Definitely partied more
than I should have,

01:06:14.104 --> 01:06:16.149
but everything I'm telling you
about Jessica is the truth.

01:06:16.173 --> 01:06:17.683
I swear to God.

01:06:17.707 --> 01:06:20.286
- I have to tell you,

01:06:20.310 --> 01:06:22.488
I have found no evidence at all

01:06:22.512 --> 01:06:25.491
that Mr. Martin's death was
anything but a suicide.

01:06:25.515 --> 01:06:29.662
- You have to look into my father's death.
- Your father?

01:06:29.686 --> 01:06:32.298
- Speak to the mechanic
who worked on his plane.

01:06:32.322 --> 01:06:35.435
- Look, if you don't
want to go to jail,

01:06:35.459 --> 01:06:37.637
you're gonna have to
make the judge believe

01:06:37.661 --> 01:06:39.672
that you're ready to
turn things around.

01:06:39.696 --> 01:06:41.707
That's what you need to
think about right now!

01:06:44.801 --> 01:06:47.737
♪♪♪

01:07:01.185 --> 01:07:03.129
- Thank you so much
for seeing me.

01:07:03.153 --> 01:07:05.165
- Of course. Is Allison OK?

01:07:05.189 --> 01:07:07.433
- All things considered,
I'd say she's doing

01:07:07.457 --> 01:07:09.359
remarkably well.

01:07:12.696 --> 01:07:15.508
I haven't seen you since...

01:07:15.532 --> 01:07:17.610
So sorry about your partner.

01:07:17.634 --> 01:07:20.546
- Thanks. As well as you
think you know someone...

01:07:20.570 --> 01:07:23.116
- We all have our
burdens to bear.

01:07:23.140 --> 01:07:26.119
- So what can I do for you?

01:07:26.143 --> 01:07:28.654
- Well, over the last few weeks,

01:07:28.678 --> 01:07:30.790
Allison and I have really
gotten to know each other.

01:07:30.814 --> 01:07:33.626
- I'm glad.

01:07:33.650 --> 01:07:35.661
- When I signed away my
rights as her mother,

01:07:35.685 --> 01:07:37.730
I was in a really bad place.

01:07:37.754 --> 01:07:39.799
I thought I was doing
the right thing.

01:07:39.823 --> 01:07:42.168
Maybe I was.

01:07:42.192 --> 01:07:44.804
I probably couldn't have given
her what she needed then,

01:07:44.828 --> 01:07:48.241
but now I can.

01:07:48.265 --> 01:07:50.476
And that's why I'd like to start
the process of adopting her.

01:07:50.500 --> 01:07:52.778
- How does Allison
feel about it?

01:07:52.802 --> 01:07:55.615
- She doesn't know yet.
It's her birthday

01:07:55.639 --> 01:07:57.574
tomorrow, and I was
hoping to surprise her.

01:07:59.809 --> 01:08:02.188
- You know that Aaron had
his reservations about you,

01:08:02.212 --> 01:08:04.357
about your motives. - I do.

01:08:04.381 --> 01:08:05.937
- And Sydni.
- Yes. I'm well aware

01:08:05.949 --> 01:08:07.517
of her conspiracy theories.

01:08:09.819 --> 01:08:12.165
I'm just so glad you were
able to get her into rehab.

01:08:12.189 --> 01:08:14.200
Hopefully now, she'll
get the help she needs.

01:08:14.224 --> 01:08:17.537
Mr. Kelton, I learned
a long time ago

01:08:17.560 --> 01:08:19.639
that there's nothing you can do
about what people think of you.

01:08:19.662 --> 01:08:23.209
All I can do is be
the best mother,

01:08:23.233 --> 01:08:25.611
the best person for Allison

01:08:25.635 --> 01:08:27.647
and trust that it's
enough for you,

01:08:27.671 --> 01:08:29.715
the courts

01:08:29.738 --> 01:08:31.684
and most importantly,

01:08:31.707 --> 01:08:33.786
my daughter.

01:08:33.810 --> 01:08:36.322
♪♪♪- Well, if it's truly

01:08:36.345 --> 01:08:38.858
what Allison wants,
you'll have my support.

01:08:38.881 --> 01:08:40.850
- Thank you.

01:08:42.919 --> 01:08:45.854
♪♪♪

01:08:54.430 --> 01:08:56.408
- Jessica.

01:08:56.433 --> 01:08:58.911
- What are you doing here?

01:08:58.935 --> 01:09:00.328
- You told me you were
coming to meet with

01:09:00.341 --> 01:09:01.747
the lawyer.
- We shouldn't be seen together.

01:09:01.770 --> 01:09:04.584
- The cops came to see me last night.
About you!

01:09:04.608 --> 01:09:07.720
Now, how the hell did
they connect us?

01:09:07.743 --> 01:09:09.822
- I don't know, but
it doesn't matter.

01:09:09.845 --> 01:09:12.325
- Yeah, it matters.
They are always looking

01:09:12.349 --> 01:09:14.894
for a reason to take me down.
- Well, if you're as good

01:09:14.917 --> 01:09:16.962
as you say you are, then they
shouldn't find anything.

01:09:16.986 --> 01:09:19.765
- You better not be thinking
about cutting me out.

01:09:19.788 --> 01:09:22.667
- Cole, relax. We're
in this together, OK?

01:09:22.692 --> 01:09:26.506
We just need to be a little
patient and keep our distance.

01:09:26.529 --> 01:09:29.442
- OK. For now.

01:09:29.466 --> 01:09:32.444
- I have to ask,

01:09:32.469 --> 01:09:34.514
are you absolutely sure you
didn't leave any loose ends?

01:09:34.537 --> 01:09:36.448
Hmm...

01:09:36.473 --> 01:09:39.843
You are my only loose end.

01:09:41.944 --> 01:09:43.846
- And you are mine.

01:10:08.705 --> 01:10:10.450
- Hey!

01:10:10.474 --> 01:10:12.518
- Hey!

01:10:12.542 --> 01:10:14.587
- It's beautiful.

01:10:14.611 --> 01:10:16.589
- Thanks. Helps keep me busy.

01:10:16.613 --> 01:10:18.758
- Yeah.

01:10:18.782 --> 01:10:20.726
This is kind of

01:10:20.750 --> 01:10:23.596
weird.

01:10:23.620 --> 01:10:26.732
- Allie won't return my calls.
- Put yourself in her place.

01:10:26.756 --> 01:10:30.470
I mean, that's her mother.

01:10:30.494 --> 01:10:31.837
- You have to help
me convince her.

01:10:31.861 --> 01:10:34.230
- Sure, but how?

01:10:36.366 --> 01:10:38.778
- We just need one solid
piece of evidence,

01:10:38.802 --> 01:10:40.813
one crack in that woman's story.

01:10:40.837 --> 01:10:42.582
- I don't know what else to do.
I mean,

01:10:42.606 --> 01:10:46.419
she didn't exactly leave
a trail of breadcrumbs.

01:10:46.443 --> 01:10:48.488
- Well, Jessica
said that she read

01:10:48.512 --> 01:10:50.590
about my dad's plane
crash in the paper.

01:10:50.614 --> 01:10:52.749
- Yeah, I remember. It
was all over the news.

01:10:55.919 --> 01:10:56.953
- Come here.

01:10:59.055 --> 01:11:01.066
So, that must be what brought

01:11:01.090 --> 01:11:03.603
her here from Seattle. - OK.

01:11:03.627 --> 01:11:05.838
- So if she planned it,
then don't you think

01:11:05.862 --> 01:11:09.342
she would have come before?
- So...?

01:11:09.366 --> 01:11:11.644
- So, if she was here before,

01:11:11.668 --> 01:11:13.746
then we could prove she's lying.

01:11:13.770 --> 01:11:16.316
- Come on, that's not anywhere
near enough for the cops.

01:11:16.340 --> 01:11:18.751
- It might be enough for Allie.

01:11:18.775 --> 01:11:21.987
♪♪♪

01:11:22.011 --> 01:11:24.056
- Do you know where
Jessica was staying?

01:11:24.080 --> 01:11:26.359
- Allie mentioned it once.

01:11:26.383 --> 01:11:30.330
She had lunch with her there.
The "Garver," I think.

01:11:30.354 --> 01:11:32.532
- I don't think I know
anyone in the kitchen there,

01:11:32.556 --> 01:11:35.835
but I must know someone
who knows someone.

01:11:35.859 --> 01:11:37.903
I might need some cash.

01:11:37.927 --> 01:11:39.896
- That's one thing I've got.

01:11:41.965 --> 01:11:46.111
♪♪♪

01:11:46.135 --> 01:11:48.605
- Hey, man.
- Yo.

01:11:53.510 --> 01:11:55.679
Thanks, man. - Yeah.

01:12:00.817 --> 01:12:03.753
♪♪♪

01:12:09.759 --> 01:12:12.605
Hey, Cole, it's me.

01:12:12.629 --> 01:12:14.574
I know what I said, but, ummm,

01:12:14.598 --> 01:12:16.466
I have something for you.

01:12:31.848 --> 01:12:34.059
- You're sure you
weren't followed?

01:12:34.083 --> 01:12:36.896
- I'm sure. Circled around
just like you said.

01:12:36.920 --> 01:12:39.164
What is this place?

01:12:39.188 --> 01:12:41.434
- I dabble in real estate.

01:12:41.458 --> 01:12:44.637
It may not be pretty,
but it's private.

01:12:44.661 --> 01:12:46.396
- Yes, it is.

01:12:49.699 --> 01:12:52.011
- Now, that's more like it.

01:12:52.035 --> 01:12:54.614
Hey.

01:12:54.638 --> 01:12:58.575
Better not be singles.
- Oh, it isn't.

01:13:05.114 --> 01:13:08.594
- You gotta be kidding me.
- Oh, I never kid about money.

01:13:08.618 --> 01:13:12.598
- Come on, Jessica, we both
know you're not a killer.

01:13:12.622 --> 01:13:14.434
That's what you need me for.

01:13:14.458 --> 01:13:16.736
- Oh?

01:13:16.760 --> 01:13:18.795
But I don't need you anymore.

01:13:20.630 --> 01:13:23.008
- Ugh! ♪♪♪

01:13:38.247 --> 01:13:41.150
♪♪♪

01:13:53.162 --> 01:13:56.165
♪♪♪

01:14:19.656 --> 01:14:22.058
- Perfect.

01:14:25.529 --> 01:14:27.196
♪♪♪- Thank you.

01:14:37.106 --> 01:14:40.019
- Hey, guys, I gotta take that.

01:14:40.043 --> 01:14:42.988
- Two. One medium.
- You were right.

01:14:43.012 --> 01:14:45.858
Jessica checked in the Garber
two weeks before the crash.

01:14:45.882 --> 01:14:48.561
Are you sure?

01:14:48.585 --> 01:14:50.863
But the guy I talked to, he
got someone to print out

01:14:53.657 --> 01:14:55.868
When can you get it?

01:14:55.892 --> 01:14:58.070
- I was gonna head over

01:14:58.094 --> 01:15:00.239
right after work tonight.

01:15:00.263 --> 01:15:03.142
I really need to get to Allie.
- And you want me to get it to her?

01:15:03.166 --> 01:15:05.778
- She has to hear it from me.
I know how to talk to her.

01:15:05.802 --> 01:15:07.813
- What are you gonna do?
Bust out of rehab?

01:15:07.837 --> 01:15:09.582
- It's not exactly maximum
security over here.

01:15:09.606 --> 01:15:11.617
Syd...

01:15:11.641 --> 01:15:14.086
is just send me right back.

01:15:14.110 --> 01:15:15.988
How soon can you be here?

01:15:16.012 --> 01:15:18.691
- ♪♪ Happy birthday

01:15:18.715 --> 01:15:20.793
♪ To you

01:15:20.817 --> 01:15:25.230
♪ Happy birthday to you

01:15:25.254 --> 01:15:27.900
♪ Happy birthday

01:15:27.924 --> 01:15:31.704
♪ Dear Allie

01:15:31.728 --> 01:15:34.239
♪ Happy birthday

01:15:34.263 --> 01:15:37.934
♪ To you ♪

01:15:40.704 --> 01:15:44.349
- Thank you, guys.
Thank you so much.

01:15:44.373 --> 01:15:46.852
I wasn't sure about celebrating

01:15:46.876 --> 01:15:49.288
today. I may have

01:15:49.312 --> 01:15:52.257
lost a lot, but...

01:15:52.281 --> 01:15:55.728
I have a lot too.

01:15:55.752 --> 01:15:59.031
- Dude, make a wish before
the fire trucks show up.

01:16:27.350 --> 01:16:29.853
♪♪♪

01:16:49.172 --> 01:16:51.274
- ♪ Bring on

01:16:56.813 --> 01:16:59.992
♪ Bring on

01:17:00.016 --> 01:17:03.829
♪♪♪- ♪ Something new

01:17:03.853 --> 01:17:06.866
♪ I'm ready to show you
all that I can do ♪

01:17:06.890 --> 01:17:09.268
♪ It's gonna be rockin'

01:17:09.292 --> 01:17:11.336
♪ That's all I can say

01:17:11.360 --> 01:17:13.673
♪ Raising a star for the world ♪

01:17:13.697 --> 01:17:15.440
♪ To meet - There you are.

01:17:15.464 --> 01:17:17.376
- Yeah. I just needed a minute.

01:17:17.400 --> 01:17:21.738
♪♪♪

01:17:24.007 --> 01:17:27.319
- Wanted to give you your gift.

01:17:27.343 --> 01:17:29.813
- What is it?
- Open it.

01:17:37.253 --> 01:17:39.298
- Does this mean...?

01:17:39.322 --> 01:17:42.325
- Means I'd very much like
to be your mother again.

01:18:03.446 --> 01:18:06.391
♪ All the way

01:18:06.415 --> 01:18:08.994
♪♪♪- I'll be right back.

01:18:09.018 --> 01:18:11.363
- ♪ It's time to get
down to the floor ♪♪

01:18:11.387 --> 01:18:13.365
- Hey, Allie!
- I'll be back in a second.

01:18:13.389 --> 01:18:16.392
♪♪♪

01:18:20.529 --> 01:18:23.075
- Allie!
- What are you doing here?

01:18:23.099 --> 01:18:24.877
- What? Did you think I was
gonna miss your birthday?

01:18:24.901 --> 01:18:28.447
- Sydni...
- OK, it's about Jessica.

01:18:28.471 --> 01:18:30.750
- Not again.
- Look. Come here, come here.

01:18:30.774 --> 01:18:33.214
Just hear me out for one second.
I have to show you something.

01:18:37.180 --> 01:18:39.291
- Her hotel bill?

01:18:39.315 --> 01:18:41.093
- Look at the date
that she checked in.

01:18:41.117 --> 01:18:45.064
Two weeks before Dad's crash.
Two weeks!

01:18:45.088 --> 01:18:47.800
- It's a mistake!
- Allie, it's not a mistake.

01:18:47.824 --> 01:18:50.502
She lied to you. She's been
lying this whole time.

01:18:50.526 --> 01:18:52.805
- There's gotta be an
explanation for this.

01:18:52.829 --> 01:18:55.340
- Look, I know this is
hard for you to hear,

01:18:55.364 --> 01:18:58.543
but all this woman
wants is your money.

01:18:58.567 --> 01:19:00.412
She couldn't even pay that bill.

01:19:00.436 --> 01:19:02.481
- She...

01:19:02.505 --> 01:19:04.373
she said she wants to adopt me.

01:19:06.810 --> 01:19:09.421
- Of course she did. Because
that would make it legal.

01:19:09.445 --> 01:19:11.523
Then your money is her money.

01:19:11.547 --> 01:19:15.151
- Allison?

01:19:18.254 --> 01:19:19.899
Sydni.

01:19:19.923 --> 01:19:22.267
- Go ahead, Allie.

01:19:22.291 --> 01:19:24.536
Ask her. Ask her why
she lied to you.

01:19:24.560 --> 01:19:26.806
- I never lied to Allison.
I'm calling the police.

01:19:26.830 --> 01:19:29.008
- Oh, good. I think
they should know too.

01:19:29.032 --> 01:19:30.967
♪♪♪- Know what?

01:19:32.969 --> 01:19:34.838
- Why did you come back here?

01:19:36.906 --> 01:19:40.152
Back to Philly? - I told you.

01:19:40.176 --> 01:19:42.045
- Tell me again.

01:19:44.013 --> 01:19:45.958
- I read about your father.

01:19:45.982 --> 01:19:49.018
♪♪♪

01:19:57.160 --> 01:19:59.996
This isn't right.
- It sure as hell isn't.

01:20:02.098 --> 01:20:04.143
- No, I meant,

01:20:04.167 --> 01:20:06.111
I read about your father
after I got here.

01:20:06.135 --> 01:20:08.347
- It's not what you said.

01:20:08.371 --> 01:20:11.416
- Allison, don't you see
what she's doing? She's just

01:20:11.440 --> 01:20:13.318
jealous of what we have.
- What's the matter?

01:20:13.342 --> 01:20:15.988
Too old to snag
another rich husband?

01:20:16.012 --> 01:20:19.624
- How dare you.
- She planned this from the start, Allie.

01:20:19.648 --> 01:20:22.261
She had Dad killed.
And Aaron too!

01:20:22.285 --> 01:20:25.297
- Allison, sweetheart,
I'm your mother.

01:20:25.321 --> 01:20:28.557
- My mother?

01:20:34.163 --> 01:20:36.232
My mother died.

01:20:38.167 --> 01:20:40.212
- Allison, please.
- Stop it, please.

01:20:40.236 --> 01:20:43.215
Just stop it! You're not
getting any of my dad's money.

01:20:43.239 --> 01:20:47.286
That's my money.

01:20:47.310 --> 01:20:49.221
Your father made me promises,
but then he left me

01:20:49.245 --> 01:20:52.191
WITH NOTHING!
- So you killed him?!

01:20:52.215 --> 01:20:53.558
- I tried talking to him.

01:20:53.582 --> 01:20:56.128
All I wanted was just

01:20:56.152 --> 01:20:58.163
a little bit to get by, but no!
He didn't listen!

01:20:58.187 --> 01:21:00.365
- How could you?!
- You have no idea

01:21:00.389 --> 01:21:02.434
what it's like, do you?
To have nothing?

01:21:02.458 --> 01:21:04.904
Of course you don't,

01:21:04.928 --> 01:21:06.671
you rich, spoiled, entitled...

01:21:06.695 --> 01:21:09.141
- GO TO HELL!

01:21:09.165 --> 01:21:10.609
- That's no way to
speak to your mother.

01:21:10.633 --> 01:21:12.912
- Back the hell off.

01:21:12.936 --> 01:21:15.014
- And you...

01:21:15.038 --> 01:21:17.917
you selfish, little bitch.

01:21:17.941 --> 01:21:20.119
- Take it easy, lady.

01:21:20.143 --> 01:21:22.178
- I should have killed you too.

01:21:26.082 --> 01:21:28.393
Leave her alone!

01:21:28.417 --> 01:21:31.130
- You should have been a good little
girl and listened to your mother!

01:21:31.154 --> 01:21:34.991
- I'm calling the cops!

01:21:40.229 --> 01:21:43.099
♪♪♪

01:22:18.501 --> 01:22:21.146
- Plus, I can ride my
bike to school from here.

01:22:21.170 --> 01:22:23.115
- So jealous.
- Allie, did you check the pie?

01:22:23.139 --> 01:22:25.017
- I lready took it
out of the oven.

01:22:25.041 --> 01:22:27.219
- Hello!

01:22:27.243 --> 01:22:30.522
- Ah, finally, the guest of honour!
Hello.

01:22:30.546 --> 01:22:32.491
- Sorry, we just
finished packing.

01:22:32.515 --> 01:22:35.294
- Sure... "packing."

01:22:35.318 --> 01:22:37.396
- You're gonna have your
hands full with that one.

01:22:37.420 --> 01:22:39.431
- Um, do you need any
help in the kitchen?

01:22:39.455 --> 01:22:43.068
- Just have to finish the salad.
- Say no more, I'm on it.

01:22:43.092 --> 01:22:45.104
- Seems like a keeper.

01:22:45.128 --> 01:22:47.739
- He just might be.
- I think

01:22:47.763 --> 01:22:51.100
your mom and dad would approve.
- Yeah, they would.

01:22:53.036 --> 01:22:55.180
- Alright, boys, let's
sit for dinner.

01:22:55.204 --> 01:22:57.182
- I can't believe I'm
already leaving tomorrow.

01:22:57.206 --> 01:22:59.784
- I know, right?
- School starts in three weeks,

01:22:59.808 --> 01:23:02.454
but I'll be back for holidays, OK?
- Plus, I can come and visit.

01:23:02.478 --> 01:23:06.325
I mean, Manhattan's only
a 19-minute train ride.

01:23:06.349 --> 01:23:08.260
- Oh, would you guys
hug it up already?

01:23:11.687 --> 01:23:14.490
- You're a pretty cool kid.
- Runs in the family.

01:23:17.426 --> 01:23:20.572
- Alright. Let's eat.

01:23:20.596 --> 01:23:22.807
- This looks delicious,
Aunt Monica.

01:23:22.831 --> 01:23:26.811
- Thanks, Allie.
- See what you'll be missing?

